The paper is about generating more massive user/item interaction data sets to bridge the gap between academic data sets and industrial production systems in Recommender System research. This topic falls under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the statistical properties of the generated data sets, which could be relevant to Statistical Learning (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes using the generated data sets to benchmark Recommender Systems, which could be relevant to Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
